-- Continental AG Plans New Bond Sale, to Issue as Much as 1.25 Billion Euros
-- B y   S o n j a   C h e u n g
-- 2010-09-27T07:27:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-27/continental-ag-plans-new-bond-sale-to-issue-as-much-as-1-25-billion-euros.html
Continental AG plans to sell as
much as 1.25 billion euros of bonds due in six and eight years,
according to a banker involved in the transaction.  Citigroup AG, Commerzbank AG, Goldmans Sachs Group Inc.,
ING Groep NV, Landesbank Baden-Wuerttemberg, Royal Bank of
Scotland Group Plc and UniCredit SpA are managing the sale of
the notes, which are callable after three years, the banker
said. The bonds are being issued through Conti-Gummi Finance BV.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sonja Cheung in London at 
 scheung58@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Reierson at 
 areierson1@bloomberg.net  